    "### Junctions (Placement Hints)\n",
    "\n",
    "- Follow the **site plan** first; refine for hydraulics.  \n",
    "- In rolling terrain, set nodes near **low points** of loops; in flat grids, spacing affects operations more than steady-state hydraulics.\n",
    "\n",
    "### Materials (Fit for Purpose)\n",
    "\n",
    "- Common choices: **Ductile Iron, PVC, HDPE, ABS**.  \n",
    "- Select by **pressure class, soil, constructability, and local standard**.  \n",
    "- Always check the **local design manual** for approved materials.\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Important Considerations for Distribution Design (At Concept Stage)\n",
    "\n",
    "Aging U.S. networks (many pipes ≈ 45 + years old) and growing communities require **targeted upgrades**. Early decisions should reflect the factors below:\n",
    "\n",
    "| **Factor** | **Why it matters** | **How it shapes design** |\n",
    "|:------------|:-------------------|:--------------------------|\n",
    "| **Age/condition** | Older assets fail more; leakage and breaks waste treated water | Prioritize **renewal** and **looping**; phase replacements |\n",
    "| **Geography & climate** | Topography, soils, freeze depth affect siting/materials | Set **zone elevations**, **cover depth**, and **material class** |\n",
    "| **Demand profile** | Average, peak, and **fire flow** drive capacity | Size **pipes/pumps/storage** for **ADD, PHD, fire flow** |\n",
    "| **Regulations** | Quality, separation, permits vary by state/city | Design to **local manuals**; meet **state/federal** rules |\n",
    "| **Budget & funding** | Scope follows funding; O&M must be sustainable | Phase projects; pursue **SRF/grants**; optimize life-cycle |\n",
    "| **Growth/expansion** | Population and land-use change over time | Provide **expandability** and **standard pipe sizes** |\n",
    "\n",
    "**Layout inputs** typically include: flows, pressures, velocities, fire flows, topography, utilities, materials, ordinances, right-of-way limits, environmental constraints, and budget. Field-operator input is invaluable for **maintainability** and **constructability**.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Schematic workflow (condensed):**\n",
    "\n",
    "1. Base grid on map  \n",
    "2. Assign demands  \n",
    "3. Add peaks + fire flow  \n",
    "4. Place storage/pumps  \n",
    "5. Simulate  \n",
    "6. Refine sizes/zones/controls  \n",
    "7. Select the **feasible** (hydraulic + economic) alternative\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Software-Aided Design (Model, Check, Iterate)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Network simulators** solve the hydraulics for all pipes, nodes, tanks, pumps, and controls.\n",
    "\n",
    "**EPANET** (free, EPA) tracks **flows, pressures, tank levels**, and **water quality/age**.  \n",
    "It supports:\n",
    "\n",
    "- Hazen–Williams, Darcy–Weisbach, and Chezy–Manning head-loss formulas  \n",
    "- Minor losses for fittings and bends  \n",
    "- Fixed or variable-speed pumps  \n",
    "- Any tank shape and flexible control rules  \n",
    "\n",
    "**Typical modeling cycle:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Build:** sources, storage, pipes, nodes, elevations, demands  \n",
    "- **Run scenarios:** *peak hour* (check min pressure), *low demand* (check max pressure), *extended period* (controls, water age)  \n",
    "- **Review:** low-pressure nodes, high-headloss pipes, storage balance  \n",
    "- **Adjust:** sizes, setpoints, elevations, or controls; re-run until criteria met  \n",
    "- **Report:** assumptions, criteria, results, and final configuration (often required for permits and funding)\n",
    "\n",
    "---\n",
    "\n",
    "## Workflow Summary (From Map to Preferred Alternative)\n",
    "\n",
    "1. **Base mapping** — surveys, contours, imagery, and field verification  \n",
    "2. **Demand projection** — average, max-day, peak-hour, and fire flow  \n",
    "3. **Tentative layout** — sources, storage, zones, mains along ROW  \n",
    "4. **Demand distribution** — assign to nodes or sub-areas  \n",
    "5. **Data encoding** — pipe lengths/diameters/roughness; node elevations/demands  \n",
    "6. **Hydraulic simulation** — steady-state + extended-period analyses  \n",
    "7. **Result review** — pressures, velocities, headloss, and storage operation  \n",
    "8. **Refinement** — adjust sizes, controls, and elevations  \n",
    "9. **Select configuration** — meets design criteria and budget  \n",
    "10. **Document** — results for permits, funding, and design development  \n",
